parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure and Unintended Vehicle Movement
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to move unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle jerks or lurches
the vehicle moves on its own
the vehicle stalls or shuts off
the transmission makes a loud whining or grinding noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle and differential can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: A loud whining or grinding noise from the rear of the vehicle
vibration while driving
difficulty shifting gears
the vehicle pulls to one side while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shifter and linkage can cause the vehicle to move unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The shifter is difficult to move
the vehicle shifts into gear on its own
the vehicle will not shift into gear
the shifter makes a loud noise or feels loose.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Worn-out brake rotors can cause extended stopping distance, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Squeaking or grinding noise when braking
pulsating brake pedal
warped rotors
and premature wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Crumbling brake pads can cause extended stopping distance, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Squeaking or grinding noise when braking
pulsating brake pedal
and premature wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause loss of braking power, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Soft or spongy brake pedal
brake pedal goes to the floor
and loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the emergency brake can cause loss of control or accidents when parking or stopping on inclines.
symptoms: Inoperable emergency brake
button and spring popped out of the emergency brake lever.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Illumination of the ABS light can indicate a problem with the anti-lock braking system, which can lead to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: ABS light illuminates on the dashboard
and loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unusual brake noise can be a sign of worn-out brake pads or rotors, which can lead to extended stopping distance or loss of control.
symptoms: Squeaking
grinding
or pulsating noise when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system, gasoline, and structure can cause a fuel leak in the event of a rear-end collision, which can lead to a fire.
symptoms: None reported
as this is a recall notice.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing belt and crankshaft can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The vehicle wants to shut off at a red light or stop sign
then kicks back into gear; the vehicle drives better on a main stretch
yet falters at slowing to a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the reverse lights can increase the risk of an accident, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intentions.
symptoms: The reverse lights failed to illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the frame rail can weaken the structure of the vehicle, increasing the risk of an accident or injury in the event of a collision.
symptoms: Corrosion on the left frame rail
but not the right.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel level sensor can cause the fuel level to read incorrectly, leading to incorrect fuel levels and potentially causing the engine to stall or fail.
symptoms: The fuel level sensor shorts out
causing the fuel level to read zero until a bump in the road causes the sensor to start operating again.
